<SECOND>PM-Shoreham-NRC,370</SECOND>
<HEAD>NRC Bars State, Local Governments from Licensing Meeting</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KIM I. MILLS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ROCKVILLE, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> Shoreham </LOCATION> nuclear power plant could have an operating license in about a month, the chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Nuclear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Regulatory </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> said after the commission ejected the affected state and local governments from its proceedings. The commission voted 4-0 Friday to remove the governments of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> state </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Suffolk </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> and the Town of <LOCATION> Southampton </LOCATION> on the grounds they `` willfully defied'' commission orders to produce documents and witnesses at licensing hearings. The federal action was unprecedented in more than 30 years of overseeing the nuclear industry. <ORGANIZATION> NRC </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Lando </PERSON> <PERSON> Zech </PERSON> said there are no further roadblocks to licensing the $ 5.4 billion plant on <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Long </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>. `` If everything were to go well, I suppose in a month would be the earliest'' for licensing, he said. <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> vowed an appeal in federal court. `` The <ORGANIZATION> Nuclear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Regulatory </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> seeks to deny the state and local governments our statutory right to protect the health and safety of our citizens,'' he said in a statement. `` The <ORGANIZATION> NRC </ORGANIZATION>'s position is absurd. Officials of the <ORGANIZATION> Long </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Island </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lighting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which owns the plant, were predictably pleased by the <ORGANIZATION> NRC </ORGANIZATION> decision. `` The <ORGANIZATION> NRC </ORGANIZATION> has proclaimed clearly and definitely that <LOCATION> Shoreham </LOCATION> is a safe plant,'' said <ORGANIZATION> LILCO </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> McDonnell </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> LILCO </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> announced Feb. 28 they had reached an agreement under which the utility would sell the plant to the state for $ 1 and it would be dismantled by the state power authority. In return, <ORGANIZATION> LILCO </ORGANIZATION> would be eligible for rate increases which have yet to be specified. Friday's ruling has clearly put <ORGANIZATION> LILCO </ORGANIZATION> in a better position to hold out for the highest rate increases it can get under the shut-down agreement. <ORGANIZATION> LILCO </ORGANIZATION> has also retained the right to continue seeking an operating license but agreed not to operate the plant even if one is granted, as long as all necessary approvals of the pact are in place by April 15. The state and local governments had stalled licensing of the reactor by refusing to participate in an emergency evacuation plan. They contended that the area around the <LOCATION> Long </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION> plant could not be evacuated in the event of an accident.
