<HEAD>International Herald Tribune President Dies Of Pneumonia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> N. </PERSON> <PERSON> Thayer </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON>, a lawyer, political adviser and corporate executive who guided the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Herald </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> in its declining years, died Saturday of pneumonia. He was 78. <PERSON> Thayer </PERSON>, who was president of the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Herald </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> and a partner in the <ORGANIZATION> Whitcom </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, was being treated at <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> when he died, according to <PERSON> Bernard </PERSON> <PERSON> Kiernan </PERSON>, a spokesman for the family. <PERSON> Thayer </PERSON> was a close associate of the late financier <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hay </PERSON> <PERSON> Whitney </PERSON>, on whose behalf <PERSON> Thayer </PERSON> arranged for the purchase of the financially troubled <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Herald </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> in 1958. Although his first job was as a newspaper reporter and he was involved in the news industry for much of his life, <PERSON> Thayer </PERSON> did not fashion himself a journalist. `` I do not have printer's ink in my blood,'' he once said. <PERSON> Kiernan </PERSON> said <PERSON> Thayer </PERSON> advised numerous politicians, including President <PERSON> Dwight </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Eisenhower </PERSON>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Mayor <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Lindsay </P