 Here are some commodity price trends for the past week: Grain and soybean futures had a mixed week on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION>. Wheat for delivery in March settled Friday at $ 4.32 -RCB- a bushel, down from $ 4.34 a week earlier; March corn rose to $ 2.78 \ a bushel from $ 2.71 -LCB-; March oats slipped to $ 2.05 -LCB- a bushel from $ 2.06 \; and March soybeans advanced to $ 7.67 -RCB- a bushel from $ Most livestock and meat futures retreated on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. April live cattle dropped to 77.80 cents a pound from 78.15 cents; March feeder cattle fell to 82.42 cents a pound from 83.62 cents; April live hogs rose to 44.15 cents a pound from 43.52 cents; and March frozen pork bellies dipped to 37.25 cents a pound from 37.42 cents. Gold and silver futures retreated on <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. April gold fell to $ 389.30 a troy ounce from $ 392.60; March silver slipped to $ 5.801 a troy ounce from $ 5.925. Energy futures gained on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. West Texas Intermediate crude oil for April delivery rose to $ 18.56 a barrel from $ 18.07; April heating oil rallied to 50.80 cents a gallon from 49.82 cents; and April unleaded gasoline advanced to 51.53 cents a gallon from 51.17 cents.
